-Hello, Lilou.

00:00:17.410 --> 00:00:19.890 align:middle line:10%
It's so nice to
be here with you.

00:00:19.890 --> 00:00:21.230 align:middle line:90%
I love Anita's story.

00:00:21.230 --> 00:00:23.310 align:middle line:84%
You probably have
seen her on the web.

00:00:23.310 --> 00:00:25.590 align:middle line:84%
I've interviewed her
many times and this

00:00:25.590 --> 00:00:29.770 align:middle line:84%
is the first time that we're
meeting in person-- so good.

00:00:29.770 --> 00:00:31.310 align:middle line:90%
It's really exciting.

00:00:31.310 --> 00:00:33.540 align:middle line:90%
It's so good to see you.

00:00:33.540 --> 00:00:37.250 align:middle line:84%
You had a near-death
experience,

00:00:37.250 --> 00:00:41.780 align:middle line:84%
an NDE, a major one, one
of the most relevant ones

00:00:41.780 --> 00:00:44.420 align:middle line:84%
that exists right now
in your reporting.

00:00:44.420 --> 00:00:46.950 align:middle line:84%
So many beautiful
things, so many

00:00:46.950 --> 00:00:50.940 align:middle line:84%
lessons that we're going to
talk about in this interview.

00:00:50.940 --> 00:00:54.060 align:middle line:84%
It's about 40-48
minute interview

00:00:54.060 --> 00:00:57.050 align:middle line:84%
here, because you're one of
the speakers of the I Can Do It

00:00:57.050 --> 00:00:58.730 align:middle line:84%
conference, organized
by Hay House.

00:00:58.730 --> 00:01:00.880 align:middle line:84%
You're going to share
the stage with Dr.

00:01:00.880 --> 00:01:05.010 align:middle line:84%
Wayne Dyer that introduced
us when I was back in Maui.

00:01:05.010 --> 00:01:08.400 align:middle line:84%
Yes, that was a
long time ago, back

00:01:08.400 --> 00:01:10.130 align:middle line:90%
before my book even came out.

00:01:10.130 --> 00:01:14.000 align:middle line:84%
But yeah, I'm really excited I'm
going to be on stage tomorrow

00:01:14.000 --> 00:01:15.340 align:middle line:90%
with Dr. Wayne Dyer.

00:01:15.340 --> 00:01:17.130 align:middle line:84%
It's going to be
really exciting.

00:01:17.130 --> 00:01:21.260 align:middle line:84%
And your story-- near-death
experiences in general right

00:01:21.260 --> 00:01:22.570 align:middle line:90%
now, this is a big topic.

00:01:22.570 --> 00:01:24.270 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of people
speak about it

00:01:24.270 --> 00:01:28.120 align:middle line:84%
and I feel very-- I feel it's
an important topic to share,

00:01:28.120 --> 00:01:30.120 align:middle line:84%
because there's a lot
of beautiful lessons

00:01:30.120 --> 00:01:36.750 align:middle line:84%
about our relationship with
time, is there life after life,

00:01:36.750 --> 00:01:43.320 align:middle line:84%
as Dr. Raymond Moody talked
about in his book back in 1975.

00:01:43.320 --> 00:01:51.100 align:middle line:84%
You went through this experience
after a cancer, a huge cancer.

00:01:51.100 --> 00:01:54.900 align:middle line:84%
It was a lymphoma grade 4B?
-That's right.

00:01:54.900 --> 00:01:57.500 align:middle line:90%
It was lymphoma grade 4B.

00:01:57.500 --> 00:02:01.660 align:middle line:84%
And I had cancer for
four years until my body

00:02:01.660 --> 00:02:03.980 align:middle line:90%
completely broke down.

00:02:03.980 --> 00:02:08.520 align:middle line:84%
And so by the time I had
the cancer four years,

00:02:08.520 --> 00:02:10.180 align:middle line:90%
my body deteriorated.

00:02:10.180 --> 00:02:13.720 align:middle line:84%
And so my muscles were
all completely wasted

00:02:13.720 --> 00:02:16.630 align:middle line:84%
and I had tumors
all over my body,

00:02:16.630 --> 00:02:21.320 align:middle line:84%
like all over my
neck and my underarms

00:02:21.320 --> 00:02:23.490 align:middle line:90%
and chest and abdomen.

00:02:23.490 --> 00:02:25.760 align:middle line:84%
And so I was
covered with tumors.

00:02:25.760 --> 00:02:30.370 align:middle line:84%
And I had fluid in my
lungs, open skin lesions.

00:02:30.370 --> 00:02:33.500 align:middle line:84%
And I was breathing
with the aid of oxygen.

00:02:33.500 --> 00:02:35.160 align:middle line:90%
And then my organs shut down.

00:02:35.160 --> 00:02:37.600 align:middle line:84%
And that's when I
went into a coma.

00:02:37.600 --> 00:02:40.380 align:middle line:84%
And it was at that time that I
had the near death experience,

00:02:40.380 --> 00:02:42.040 align:middle line:84%
because the doctors
told my family

00:02:42.040 --> 00:02:45.390 align:middle line:84%
that these were my final
hours and that I was dying.

00:02:45.390 --> 00:02:48.970 align:middle line:84%
That was in 2002 you were
diagnosed, and then in 2006

00:02:48.970 --> 00:02:52.160 align:middle line:84%
that's when you went
into the coma state.

00:02:52.160 --> 00:02:53.760 align:middle line:90%
Yes, that's exactly right.

00:02:53.760 --> 00:02:56.930 align:middle line:84%
So I was diagnosed
in April, 2002.

00:02:56.930 --> 00:03:02.500 align:middle line:84%
And it was February the second,
2006 that I went into a coma.

00:03:02.500 --> 00:03:05.910 align:middle line:84%
And even though I
was in a coma though,

00:03:05.910 --> 00:03:09.910 align:middle line:84%
I was aware of everything
that was happening around me.

00:03:09.910 --> 00:03:15.890 align:middle line:84%
It was as though I was more
awake or alert than normal.

00:03:15.890 --> 00:03:19.260 align:middle line:84%
Did it go in and out, in and
out before you completely went

00:03:19.260 --> 00:03:21.230 align:middle line:90%
into this experience?

00:03:21.230 --> 00:03:22.665 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, interestingly it was.

00:03:22.665 --> 00:03:26.480 align:middle line:84%
It started out as though--
I felt as though I was--

00:03:26.480 --> 00:03:28.200 align:middle line:84%
I thought I was
drifting in and out

00:03:28.200 --> 00:03:30.760 align:middle line:84%
of consciousness, because
I was aware of what

00:03:30.760 --> 00:03:33.050 align:middle line:90%
was happening on this side.

00:03:33.050 --> 00:03:36.040 align:middle line:84%
And then I was aware of
things on the other side.

00:03:36.040 --> 00:03:40.580 align:middle line:84%
Like I encountered my
father, who had passed away

00:03:40.580 --> 00:03:42.380 align:middle line:90%
about 10 years before that.

00:03:42.380 --> 00:03:44.100 align:middle line:84%
I encountered my
best friend who had

00:03:44.100 --> 00:03:46.090 align:middle line:90%
passed away two years before.

00:03:46.090 --> 00:03:47.740 align:middle line:84%
And then I was aware
of everything that

00:03:47.740 --> 00:03:49.090 align:middle line:90%
was happening in this side.

00:03:49.090 --> 00:03:51.320 align:middle line:84%
So to me, it felt
like I was drifting

00:03:51.320 --> 00:03:53.340 align:middle line:90%
in and out, in and out.

00:03:53.340 --> 00:03:57.480 align:middle line:84%
But much later, after I came
out of the coma completely,

00:03:57.480 --> 00:04:01.860 align:middle line:84%
I found out from doctors and
family that I was in the coma

00:04:01.860 --> 00:04:02.720 align:middle line:90%
the whole time.

00:04:02.720 --> 00:04:07.040 align:middle line:84%
I was like not here
the whole time.

00:04:07.040 --> 00:04:09.730 align:middle line:84%
Your heart was
actually stopped or not?

00:04:09.730 --> 00:04:12.240 align:middle line:90%
No, my heart was still beating.

00:04:12.240 --> 00:04:17.850 align:middle line:84%
But my breathing was
aided with the machine.

00:04:17.850 --> 00:04:20.930 align:middle line:84%
So I was breathing with the
aid of the oxygen machine.

00:04:20.930 --> 00:04:25.670 align:middle line:84%
And my heart was still beating
and there were the machines

00:04:25.670 --> 00:04:29.520 align:middle line:84%
and Danny was watching the
machine the whole night just--

00:04:29.520 --> 00:04:30.220 align:middle line:90%
Danny, your husband?

00:04:30.220 --> 00:04:32.780 align:middle line:84%
Yes, Danny my husband--
just to make sure

00:04:32.780 --> 00:04:34.080 align:middle line:90%
that I didn't stop breathing.

00:04:34.080 --> 00:04:37.160 align:middle line:84%
And basically, my family
were waiting, thinking

00:04:37.160 --> 00:04:40.390 align:middle line:90%
that these were my last hours.

00:04:40.390 --> 00:04:41.780 align:middle line:84%
The skeptic, of
course-- there's

00:04:41.780 --> 00:04:44.290 align:middle line:84%
a lot of people that are skeptic
about near-death experience.

00:04:44.290 --> 00:04:46.440 align:middle line:84%
They speak out, the
drugs could induce

00:04:46.440 --> 00:04:47.720 align:middle line:90%
those kind of experience.

00:04:47.720 --> 00:04:49.770 align:middle line:90%
Do you think it was your case?

00:04:49.770 --> 00:04:53.320 align:middle line:84%
The thing is that there
will always be skeptics.

00:04:53.320 --> 00:04:59.310 align:middle line:84%
And my reaction is
that I'm actually

00:04:59.310 --> 00:05:02.860 align:middle line:84%
not trying to convince
anyone of anything,

00:05:02.860 --> 00:05:05.510 align:middle line:90%
because I have nothing.

00:05:05.510 --> 00:05:08.160 align:middle line:84%
I'm not trying to sell
anything or convince anyone.

00:05:08.160 --> 00:05:10.840 align:middle line:84%
I'm only sharing
what happened to me.

00:05:10.840 --> 00:05:14.620 align:middle line:84%
The only thing that
I have proof for

00:05:14.620 --> 00:05:18.440 align:middle line:84%
is the fact that my cancer,
the healing from my cancer

00:05:18.440 --> 00:05:19.670 align:middle line:90%
was dramatic.

00:05:19.670 --> 00:05:24.020 align:middle line:84%
But there's no way to prove
that what I experienced

00:05:24.020 --> 00:05:26.570 align:middle line:84%
in the other realm
was real or whether it

00:05:26.570 --> 00:05:28.360 align:middle line:90%
was the drugs or anything.

00:05:28.360 --> 00:05:30.930 align:middle line:90%
There's no way to prove that.

00:05:30.930 --> 00:05:33.290 align:middle line:84%
Everybody knows that
I was in the hospital,

00:05:33.290 --> 00:05:34.670 align:middle line:90%
that I was unconscious.

00:05:34.670 --> 00:05:37.400 align:middle line:84%
The medical records show
that I was unconscious.

00:05:37.400 --> 00:05:39.870 align:middle line:84%
Everybody knows I was
supposed to die that night.

00:05:39.870 --> 00:05:41.650 align:middle line:90%
That's what the records show.

00:05:41.650 --> 00:05:44.040 align:middle line:84%
And the records show
that I came out of it

00:05:44.040 --> 00:05:46.420 align:middle line:90%
and I healed very quickly.

00:05:46.420 --> 00:05:49.740 align:middle line:84%
You remember the
conversation that happened.

00:05:49.740 --> 00:05:53.230 align:middle line:84%
You even saw your brother
flying in to come and see you.

00:05:53.230 --> 00:05:57.630 align:middle line:84%
You felt what they
felt. You heard them.

00:05:57.630 --> 00:05:58.390 align:middle line:90%
You felt them.

00:05:58.390 --> 00:06:04.130 align:middle line:84%
Tell us about this omnipresent
type of experience.

00:06:04.130 --> 00:06:07.430 align:middle line:84%
Oh it was like-- it
was an incredible,

00:06:07.430 --> 00:06:10.360 align:middle line:90%
incredible experience.

00:06:10.360 --> 00:06:15.320 align:middle line:84%
It was like my consciousness--
it was like I was no

00:06:15.320 --> 00:06:17.800 align:middle line:90%
longer restrained by my body.

00:06:17.800 --> 00:06:23.060 align:middle line:84%
And it was like I just
expanded beyond my body

00:06:23.060 --> 00:06:29.670 align:middle line:84%
and I was feeling really light
and free and no longer in pain,

00:06:29.670 --> 00:06:32.760 align:middle line:84%
no longer encumbered
by the cancer.

00:06:32.760 --> 00:06:36.450 align:middle line:84%
It was just such an
amazing, amazing feeling.

00:06:36.450 --> 00:06:43.970 align:middle line:84%
And then I just expanded
and I felt like I was loved.

00:06:43.970 --> 00:06:47.920 align:middle line:84%
I use the word "loved," but it's
not exactly what describes it.

00:06:47.920 --> 00:06:51.400 align:middle line:84%
But I felt like I was
unconditionally loved,

00:06:51.400 --> 00:06:53.930 align:middle line:84%
like I didn't have
to prove myself

00:06:53.930 --> 00:06:56.840 align:middle line:90%
or work hard at being loved.

00:06:56.840 --> 00:06:58.840 align:middle line:84%
I didn't have to
work at being worthy.

00:06:58.840 --> 00:07:02.630 align:middle line:84%
I was just loved, just
because I existed.

00:07:02.630 --> 00:07:06.110 align:middle line:84%
And that was just the
most amazing feeling.

00:07:06.110 --> 00:07:11.070 align:middle line:84%
Even though if you were
feeling the fear and the pain

00:07:11.070 --> 00:07:13.870 align:middle line:84%
of other people around
and even the doctors,

00:07:13.870 --> 00:07:16.420 align:middle line:84%
you could hear a conversation
in a different room.

00:07:16.420 --> 00:07:17.380 align:middle line:90%
Is that right?

00:07:17.380 --> 00:07:19.160 align:middle line:84%
So you would hear
what was happening,

00:07:19.160 --> 00:07:21.060 align:middle line:90%
but you felt nothing but love.

00:07:21.060 --> 00:07:25.440 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, I felt nothing but
love for myself, and for them.

00:07:25.440 --> 00:07:27.610 align:middle line:84%
I was able to hear
the conversations

00:07:27.610 --> 00:07:31.580 align:middle line:84%
and every single
thing the doctors did.

00:07:31.580 --> 00:07:35.360 align:middle line:84%
I was aware of every procedure,
of them poking needles

00:07:35.360 --> 00:07:38.970 align:middle line:84%
into my veins and removing
fluid from my lungs,

00:07:38.970 --> 00:07:40.720 align:middle line:84%
because my lungs were
filled with fluid

00:07:40.720 --> 00:07:43.150 align:middle line:90%
and I was choking on my fluid.

00:07:43.150 --> 00:07:46.420 align:middle line:84%
And the doctors were putting
a needle in through my back

00:07:46.420 --> 00:07:47.730 align:middle line:90%
and removing the fluid.

00:07:47.730 --> 00:07:50.310 align:middle line:84%
I was aware of everything
they were doing,

00:07:50.310 --> 00:07:53.600 align:middle line:84%
conversations they were having,
even conversations that took

00:07:53.600 --> 00:07:57.370 align:middle line:84%
place outside the room, which
I was able to relate to them

00:07:57.370 --> 00:07:59.560 align:middle line:84%
after, which really
shocked them.

00:07:59.560 --> 00:08:02.170 align:middle line:84%
The doctor was really
shocked when I came out

00:08:02.170 --> 00:08:05.320 align:middle line:84%
of the coma, when I actually
told him that you had come

00:08:05.320 --> 00:08:08.700 align:middle line:84%
into my room at about 4:00
or 5:00 AM in the morning

00:08:08.700 --> 00:08:10.620 align:middle line:84%
and you took fluid
out of my lungs.

00:08:10.620 --> 00:08:12.290 align:middle line:90%
And he was really surprised.

00:08:12.290 --> 00:08:13.950 align:middle line:84%
He said, but you
were unconscious.

00:08:13.950 --> 00:08:15.460 align:middle line:90%
How would you know that?

00:08:15.460 --> 00:08:17.470 align:middle line:90%
And I said, I felt everything.

00:08:17.470 --> 00:08:19.730 align:middle line:90%
I saw it all.

00:08:19.730 --> 00:08:22.530 align:middle line:84%
But yeah, I felt everything
they were feeling.

00:08:22.530 --> 00:08:26.080 align:middle line:84%
It's like as though we
share one consciousness.

00:08:26.080 --> 00:08:29.160 align:middle line:84%
So I could feel what
my family was feeling.

00:08:29.160 --> 00:08:32.490 align:middle line:84%
I could feel what every
doctor and nurse was feeling.

00:08:32.490 --> 00:08:34.370 align:middle line:84%
But even though I could feel
what they were feeling--

00:08:34.370 --> 00:08:37.140 align:middle line:84%
I could feel their
fear or their anxiety,

00:08:37.140 --> 00:08:39.409 align:middle line:84%
I could feel my
family's sadness.

00:08:39.409 --> 00:08:42.100 align:middle line:84%
All I felt for
them, all of them,

00:08:42.100 --> 00:08:46.150 align:middle line:84%
was just unconditional
love and empathy.

00:08:46.150 --> 00:08:50.820 align:middle line:84%
I could just feel-- I was
just emphasizing with them.

00:08:50.820 --> 00:08:54.230 align:middle line:84%
Do you know if people around
you felt a similar experience?

00:08:54.230 --> 00:08:58.140 align:middle line:84%
Because more and more now,
we talk about shared NDEs.

00:08:58.140 --> 00:09:00.400 align:middle line:84%
So sometimes people
in the room could feel

00:09:00.400 --> 00:09:01.720 align:middle line:90%
that something is happening.

00:09:01.720 --> 00:09:04.180 align:middle line:84%
Did they have any idea what
you were going through,

00:09:04.180 --> 00:09:06.880 align:middle line:84%
or you had to report
it once you came back?

00:09:06.880 --> 00:09:10.460 align:middle line:84%
The people around me,
they didn't have any idea

00:09:10.460 --> 00:09:11.540 align:middle line:90%
what I was going through.

00:09:11.540 --> 00:09:16.320 align:middle line:84%
But the interesting thing is,
my brother, who was in India,

00:09:16.320 --> 00:09:19.340 align:middle line:84%
even before my mother
called him to say

00:09:19.340 --> 00:09:22.380 align:middle line:84%
that I had gone into a coma
and he should come here,

00:09:22.380 --> 00:09:23.820 align:middle line:90%
he felt something.

00:09:23.820 --> 00:09:27.520 align:middle line:84%
So even before my mother
or husband called them,

00:09:27.520 --> 00:09:30.910 align:middle line:84%
he just felt something
was wrong that morning

00:09:30.910 --> 00:09:32.630 align:middle line:90%
when I went into a coma.

00:09:32.630 --> 00:09:37.630 align:middle line:84%
And he immediately went to
get on a flight to Hong Kong.

00:09:37.630 --> 00:09:41.030 align:middle line:84%
And he couldn't get a flight
in the town that he was in.

00:09:41.030 --> 00:09:45.100 align:middle line:84%
He drove four hours out of
his town to the next town

00:09:45.100 --> 00:09:48.890 align:middle line:84%
to get on a flight to come
to Hong Kong to see me.

00:09:48.890 --> 00:09:53.680 align:middle line:84%
And it was while he was in
the car going to that airport

00:09:53.680 --> 00:09:56.560 align:middle line:84%
that he got the phone
call from a family member

00:09:56.560 --> 00:09:58.260 align:middle line:84%
to tell him to
hurry up and come.

00:09:58.260 --> 00:10:00.140 align:middle line:84%
And he said, oh, I'm
already on my way.

00:10:00.140 --> 00:10:02.000 align:middle line:90%
I sensed something was wrong.

00:10:02.000 --> 00:10:04.260 align:middle line:84%
So during my
near-death experience,

00:10:04.260 --> 00:10:07.410 align:middle line:84%
I was connecting
with my brother.

00:10:07.410 --> 00:10:09.450 align:middle line:90%
And he felt it.

00:10:09.450 --> 00:10:13.550 align:middle line:84%
He actually felt something
to rush and come to see me.

00:10:13.550 --> 00:10:16.810 align:middle line:84%
And there was a part of me that
was already connecting with him

00:10:16.810 --> 00:10:20.920 align:middle line:84%
and not wanting to die until he
came, because I didn't want him

00:10:20.920 --> 00:10:24.960 align:middle line:84%
to come and feel really sad
or guilty that it was too

00:10:24.960 --> 00:10:27.260 align:middle line:90%
late, that I'd already gone.

00:10:27.260 --> 00:10:29.080 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to wait
until he got here.

00:10:29.080 --> 00:10:31.610 align:middle line:90%
And it was like he sensed that.

00:10:31.610 --> 00:10:34.905 align:middle line:84%
So you were thinking that, or
you wanted him to think that,

00:10:34.905 --> 00:10:37.900 align:middle line:84%
or how did you actually
communicate it from that way,

00:10:37.900 --> 00:10:42.010 align:middle line:90%
from your state to his?

00:10:42.010 --> 00:10:43.170 align:middle line:90%
Do you remember?

00:10:43.170 --> 00:10:46.000 align:middle line:84%
Well, I remember
I was thinking it.

00:10:46.000 --> 00:10:51.610 align:middle line:84%
And then I wasn't thinking it
with the intention of sending

00:10:51.610 --> 00:10:53.680 align:middle line:90%
it to him, but he got it.

00:10:53.680 --> 00:10:57.120 align:middle line:84%
So I was thinking it
for myself, to myself.

00:10:57.120 --> 00:10:59.350 align:middle line:84%
I was thinking, I
mustn't die yet.

00:10:59.350 --> 00:11:01.820 align:middle line:84%
I must wait until my
brother gets here,

00:11:01.820 --> 00:11:04.470 align:middle line:84%
because he will feel
terrible if he gets here

00:11:04.470 --> 00:11:06.230 align:middle line:90%
