It means stopping all that.

00:21:40.090 --> 00:21:43.680 align:middle line:84%
That's when you start
to feel invincible.

00:21:43.680 --> 00:21:45.910 align:middle line:84%
It feels like nearly
scary to just know that,

00:21:45.910 --> 00:21:49.710 align:middle line:84%
because of like, who am I,
then the question comes.

00:21:49.710 --> 00:21:51.860 align:middle line:84%
That's a big question
that people ask is,

00:21:51.860 --> 00:21:54.870 align:middle line:90%
OK, under all that, who am I?

00:21:54.870 --> 00:21:59.960 align:middle line:84%
The clue is to look for
what makes you really happy,

00:21:59.960 --> 00:22:02.430 align:middle line:90%
what makes your heart sing.

00:22:02.430 --> 00:22:06.580 align:middle line:84%
And if you just even ask
yourself this question,

00:22:06.580 --> 00:22:08.650 align:middle line:84%
because I always say,
it's really important

00:22:08.650 --> 00:22:09.600 align:middle line:90%
to love yourself.

00:22:09.600 --> 00:22:13.750 align:middle line:84%
And people say, how do I
even start to love yourself?

00:22:13.750 --> 00:22:15.870 align:middle line:90%
So ask yourself this question.

00:22:15.870 --> 00:22:20.940 align:middle line:84%
If I loved myself, what
would I do right now?

00:22:20.940 --> 00:22:24.410 align:middle line:84%
When I wake up in the morning,
what would I spend my time

00:22:24.410 --> 00:22:27.980 align:middle line:84%
doing if I was someone
that really, really

00:22:27.980 --> 00:22:31.640 align:middle line:84%
loved, valued, treasured,
and respected myself,

00:22:31.640 --> 00:22:33.280 align:middle line:90%
what would I be doing?

00:22:33.280 --> 00:22:34.620 align:middle line:84%
And that's the
question to answer.

00:22:34.620 --> 00:22:37.980 align:middle line:84%
And that's your clue as
to who you really are.

00:22:37.980 --> 00:22:41.200 align:middle line:84%
And then allowing within that,
because a lot of people as you

00:22:41.200 --> 00:22:43.830 align:middle line:84%
saying, are searching
for their purpose,

00:22:43.830 --> 00:22:48.330 align:middle line:84%
would love to contribute,
would love to be on target

00:22:48.330 --> 00:22:49.860 align:middle line:90%
and have things flowing.

00:22:49.860 --> 00:22:53.600 align:middle line:84%
But within that,
it's also allowing.

00:22:53.600 --> 00:22:55.240 align:middle line:90%
It absolutely is allowing.

00:22:55.240 --> 00:23:02.000 align:middle line:84%
Because again, if we feel
the need to go pursuing,

00:23:02.000 --> 00:23:06.780 align:middle line:84%
chasing aggressively going after
what we want, again, what we're

00:23:06.780 --> 00:23:09.700 align:middle line:84%
doing is we're even sending
ourselves the message

00:23:09.700 --> 00:23:11.180 align:middle line:84%
that we're not
good enough and we

00:23:11.180 --> 00:23:14.780 align:middle line:84%
need to work really hard to
compete with everyone else

00:23:14.780 --> 00:23:17.290 align:middle line:84%
and to aggressively
pursue what we want.

00:23:17.290 --> 00:23:21.580 align:middle line:84%
But in truth, you deserve
and you are worthy

00:23:21.580 --> 00:23:24.110 align:middle line:84%
and you deserve to have
everything that is yours.

00:23:24.110 --> 00:23:27.160 align:middle line:84%
So all you have to
do is if you love

00:23:27.160 --> 00:23:30.590 align:middle line:84%
yourself, what is
yours-- you will

00:23:30.590 --> 00:23:32.850 align:middle line:90%
actually attract what is yours.

00:23:32.850 --> 00:23:35.490 align:middle line:84%
So you know how
many of us believe

00:23:35.490 --> 00:23:39.510 align:middle line:84%
that our thoughts attract
our reality or are

00:23:39.510 --> 00:23:41.410 align:middle line:90%
thoughts create our reality?

00:23:41.410 --> 00:23:44.190 align:middle line:84%
I would go one step
further and to say,

00:23:44.190 --> 00:23:47.020 align:middle line:84%
it's our thoughts
about ourselves

00:23:47.020 --> 00:23:49.100 align:middle line:90%
that create our reality.

00:23:49.100 --> 00:23:51.860 align:middle line:84%
The more you love
yourself, the more

00:23:51.860 --> 00:23:54.000 align:middle line:90%
other people will love you.

00:23:54.000 --> 00:23:58.710 align:middle line:84%
The more you hate yourself for
disrespect yourself or treat

00:23:58.710 --> 00:24:01.940 align:middle line:84%
yourself badly, the more
other people will also

00:24:01.940 --> 00:24:04.790 align:middle line:90%
not respect you or trod on you.

00:24:04.790 --> 00:24:06.770 align:middle line:84%
So it's your thoughts
about yourself

00:24:06.770 --> 00:24:09.140 align:middle line:90%
that's really important.

00:24:09.140 --> 00:24:12.890 align:middle line:84%
Tell us about this lady
that you had on the radio

00:24:12.890 --> 00:24:15.810 align:middle line:84%
and you spoke of unconditional
love and relationship.

00:24:15.810 --> 00:24:18.030 align:middle line:84%
Let's go into this,
because I feel

00:24:18.030 --> 00:24:21.950 align:middle line:84%
it's really aligned with
where we're at right now

00:24:21.950 --> 00:24:23.350 align:middle line:90%
in this conversation.

00:24:23.350 --> 00:24:25.550 align:middle line:90%
Sure, I'd love to.

00:24:25.550 --> 00:24:28.290 align:middle line:84%
In fact, this started
out as a message

00:24:28.290 --> 00:24:31.780 align:middle line:84%
for a specific person
who was having a problem

00:24:31.780 --> 00:24:32.790 align:middle line:90%
in their relationship.

00:24:32.790 --> 00:24:36.500 align:middle line:84%
And what I wanted to do was I
wanted to share the difference

00:24:36.500 --> 00:24:41.480 align:middle line:84%
between the kind of love that
normally we as physical humans

00:24:41.480 --> 00:24:44.520 align:middle line:84%
have in a relationship,
versus unconditional love.

00:24:44.520 --> 00:24:47.100 align:middle line:84%
Normally in a
human relationship,

00:24:47.100 --> 00:24:50.670 align:middle line:84%
we expect a lot
of loyalty and we

00:24:50.670 --> 00:24:56.700 align:middle line:84%
sign contracts such as legal,
marital contracts and so on.

00:24:56.700 --> 00:25:01.980 align:middle line:84%
And this is kind of like
there's an expectation.

00:25:01.980 --> 00:25:04.810 align:middle line:84%
This is what I call
the conditional love.

00:25:04.810 --> 00:25:08.320 align:middle line:84%
And I will stay with you out
of loyalty, out of obligation,

00:25:08.320 --> 00:25:12.140 align:middle line:84%
and so on, even
when we get older.

00:25:12.140 --> 00:25:16.820 align:middle line:84%
Now, true unconditional
love is-- oh,

00:25:16.820 --> 00:25:20.250 align:middle line:84%
and also the other thing
is, very often when we meet

00:25:20.250 --> 00:25:22.130 align:middle line:84%
somebody that we
want to marry or we

00:25:22.130 --> 00:25:24.400 align:middle line:84%
want to spend the rest
of our lives with,

00:25:24.400 --> 00:25:27.440 align:middle line:84%
it's because that person
makes us feel good.

00:25:27.440 --> 00:25:32.290 align:middle line:84%
And when a person leaves
us and we want them back,

00:25:32.290 --> 00:25:34.790 align:middle line:90%
it's because we feel good.

00:25:34.790 --> 00:25:38.760 align:middle line:84%
It makes us feel good
to have them back.

00:25:38.760 --> 00:25:42.380 align:middle line:84%
When you truly love
somebody unconditionally,

00:25:42.380 --> 00:25:45.840 align:middle line:84%
you want for them
what they want.

00:25:45.840 --> 00:25:49.530 align:middle line:84%
When you don't love
someone unconditionally,

00:25:49.530 --> 00:25:53.950 align:middle line:84%
and when you only
want-- when you only

00:25:53.950 --> 00:25:56.830 align:middle line:84%
love someone because
it's what you want,

00:25:56.830 --> 00:25:58.360 align:middle line:90%
you think you love them.

00:25:58.360 --> 00:26:03.230 align:middle line:84%
But actually, you are not
loving them unconditionally.

00:26:03.230 --> 00:26:06.300 align:middle line:84%
So true unconditional
love is when

00:26:06.300 --> 00:26:09.930 align:middle line:84%
you want for the other person
what they want for themselves.

00:26:09.930 --> 00:26:13.270 align:middle line:84%
So if somebody wants
to leave a relationship

00:26:13.270 --> 00:26:16.110 align:middle line:84%
but you still want them
in the relationship,

00:26:16.110 --> 00:26:20.580 align:middle line:84%
and there's a problem, what
I would like to see people do

00:26:20.580 --> 00:26:24.920 align:middle line:84%
is to actually have a
dialogue where you can say

00:26:24.920 --> 00:26:28.110 align:middle line:84%
to the other person, where
you can say to your partner

00:26:28.110 --> 00:26:31.920 align:middle line:90%
that I love you unconditionally.

00:26:31.920 --> 00:26:37.840 align:middle line:84%
And I want you to have for
yourself what you want.

00:26:37.840 --> 00:26:43.860 align:middle line:84%
And at the same time, if what
you want is something that

00:26:43.860 --> 00:26:47.400 align:middle line:84%
doesn't resonate with
me-- in other words,

00:26:47.400 --> 00:26:50.420 align:middle line:84%
you cannot have another
partner and still

00:26:50.420 --> 00:26:52.240 align:middle line:90%
expect me to hang around.

00:26:52.240 --> 00:26:57.650 align:middle line:84%
I love myself enough that if
I can't accept what you want,

00:26:57.650 --> 00:27:01.450 align:middle line:84%
I love myself enough to
leave the relationship,

00:27:01.450 --> 00:27:05.370 align:middle line:84%
to not hang around
and be mistreated.

00:27:05.370 --> 00:27:07.350 align:middle line:84%
And you think we should
have those conversations

00:27:07.350 --> 00:27:08.850 align:middle line:90%
in relationships?

00:27:08.850 --> 00:27:12.240 align:middle line:84%
I think that if it's a
problematical relationship,

00:27:12.240 --> 00:27:16.370 align:middle line:84%
if there is some problems, I
think that if two people really

00:27:16.370 --> 00:27:20.080 align:middle line:84%
want to get honest and
real with each other,

00:27:20.080 --> 00:27:25.320 align:middle line:84%
they need to be brave enough to
actually say to their partner

00:27:25.320 --> 00:27:29.730 align:middle line:84%
that I want to know what you
want in the relationship.

00:27:29.730 --> 00:27:32.060 align:middle line:84%
Because currently,
what we're doing

00:27:32.060 --> 00:27:35.350 align:middle line:84%
and why very often we have
problematic relationships

00:27:35.350 --> 00:27:38.480 align:middle line:84%
is because at the
moment, it's about what

00:27:38.480 --> 00:27:42.000 align:middle line:84%
I want in the relationship
and I'm not getting it met.

00:27:42.000 --> 00:27:44.340 align:middle line:90%
And therefore, I'm not happy.

00:27:44.340 --> 00:27:47.050 align:middle line:84%
So what we need to ask
each other and to listen

00:27:47.050 --> 00:27:50.840 align:middle line:84%
is, I want to know what you
want in the relationship.

00:27:50.840 --> 00:27:54.770 align:middle line:84%
And I love you enough for
you to actually achieve it.

00:27:54.770 --> 00:27:56.420 align:middle line:90%
But it has to be mutual.

00:27:56.420 --> 00:28:00.930 align:middle line:84%
And then the partner has to say
that to you-- what do you want,

00:28:00.930 --> 00:28:03.460 align:middle line:84%
and I love you
enough to make sure

00:28:03.460 --> 00:28:05.010 align:middle line:90%
that you get what you want.

00:28:05.010 --> 00:28:07.770 align:middle line:84%
So in other words,
if two people really

00:28:07.770 --> 00:28:11.650 align:middle line:84%
love each other unconditionally
in a relationship,

00:28:11.650 --> 00:28:17.960 align:middle line:84%
my part in your relationship is
to allow you to be you so you

00:28:17.960 --> 00:28:19.670 align:middle line:90%
can achieve what you want.

00:28:19.670 --> 00:28:23.520 align:middle line:84%
Your part is to allow me
to be me with no judgment,

00:28:23.520 --> 00:28:25.620 align:middle line:90%
so I can achieve what I want.

00:28:25.620 --> 00:28:28.807 align:middle line:84%
And that's true
unconditional love.

00:28:28.807 --> 00:28:30.040 align:middle line:84%
It feels like it
takes a lot to have

00:28:30.040 --> 00:28:32.620 align:middle line:90%
two people on that same level.

00:28:32.620 --> 00:28:35.630 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, but I feel that's the
relationship of the future.

00:28:35.630 --> 00:28:38.470 align:middle line:84%
Because today, so
many relationships

00:28:38.470 --> 00:28:40.300 align:middle line:90%
are crumbling, so many.

00:28:40.300 --> 00:28:42.050 align:middle line:84%
Or not even meant
to be, I feel.

00:28:42.050 --> 00:28:43.760 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, not even meant to be.

00:28:43.760 --> 00:28:46.090 align:middle line:84%
And I think the
relationship of the future

00:28:46.090 --> 00:28:49.660 align:middle line:84%
truly will be based
on this level of love,

00:28:49.660 --> 00:28:53.450 align:middle line:84%
where I want to be
with you because I

00:28:53.450 --> 00:28:55.220 align:middle line:90%
love you for who you are.

00:28:55.220 --> 00:28:57.820 align:middle line:84%
And my being with
you will always

00:28:57.820 --> 00:29:00.980 align:middle line:90%
allow you to be who you are.

00:29:00.980 --> 00:29:07.920 align:middle line:84%
This is kind of valid for
everything in our life, at work

00:29:07.920 --> 00:29:13.300 align:middle line:84%
but also with our health and
the kind of food that we eat.

00:29:13.300 --> 00:29:17.730 align:middle line:84%
And there's so many things
that we're expecting

00:29:17.730 --> 00:29:21.370 align:middle line:84%
or we want in life, but
then we're not really

00:29:21.370 --> 00:29:23.480 align:middle line:84%
stepping in fully
and daring to have

00:29:23.480 --> 00:29:26.410 align:middle line:84%
those authentic conversations
and daring to speak our truth.

00:29:26.410 --> 00:29:29.700 align:middle line:84%
Or we're waiting for
others to do their part

00:29:29.700 --> 00:29:32.420 align:middle line:84%
and to be the leaders
and transform this world.

00:29:32.420 --> 00:29:37.940 align:middle line:84%
But really, your message
in its essence is, wake up.

00:29:37.940 --> 00:29:40.280 align:middle line:90%
This your time.

00:29:40.280 --> 00:29:44.250 align:middle line:84%
This is your time to shine
and live fully and love.

00:29:44.250 --> 00:29:45.740 align:middle line:90%
Yes, exactly.

00:29:45.740 --> 00:29:48.940 align:middle line:84%
It's daring to actually
take charge of your life.

00:29:48.940 --> 00:29:52.020 align:middle line:84%
I think many of us are
very ready to blame people.

00:29:52.020 --> 00:29:54.350 align:middle line:84%
We blame our parents
for how we turned out.

00:29:54.350 --> 00:29:57.780 align:middle line:84%
We blame our relationships,
our partners, our spouses.

00:29:57.780 --> 00:30:02.400 align:middle line:84%
And this is what I mean, is that
if your partner does not allow

00:30:02.400 --> 00:30:05.460 align:middle line:84%
you to be who you
are, you need to love

00:30:05.460 --> 00:30:08.940 align:middle line:84%
yourself enough also to not
be treated like a doormat.

00:30:08.940 --> 00:30:11.650 align:middle line:84%
So it's really daring
to take charge.

00:30:11.650 --> 00:30:13.040 align:middle line:90%
Stop blaming.

00:30:13.040 --> 00:30:15.870 align:middle line:84%
Even stop blaming all
the big corporates,

00:30:15.870 --> 00:30:19.390 align:middle line:84%
because we support those big
corporates by buying into them.

00:30:19.390 --> 00:30:22.550 align:middle line:84%
Stop blaming them and
stop buying into it.

00:30:22.550 --> 00:30:23.550 align:middle line:90%
Here's what I say.

00:30:23.550 --> 00:30:27.490 align:middle line:84%
The big message is that when
you love yourself enough,

00:30:27.490 --> 00:30:29.630 align:middle line:84%
you will not control
other people.

00:30:29.630 --> 00:30:33.820 align:middle line:84%
But you will also not allow
other people to control you.

00:30:33.820 --> 00:30:37.350 align:middle line:90%
So dare to be yourself.

00:30:37.350 --> 00:30:38.050 align:middle line:90%
Whoa.

00:30:38.050 --> 00:30:39.300 align:middle line:90%
This is a big lesson.

00:30:39.300 --> 00:30:41.890 align:middle line:84%
And I know you're
living this truth

00:30:41.890 --> 00:30:45.060 align:middle line:84%
and you must be
thrilled to see how

00:30:45.060 --> 00:30:48.200 align:middle line:84%
your life is unfolding
in a much bigger way

00:30:48.200 --> 00:30:49.430 align:middle line:90%
than you could even expect.

00:30:49.430 --> 00:30:51.540 align:middle line:84%
You knew coming back that
something will happen

00:30:51.540 --> 00:30:54.060 align:middle line:84%
and something will
be taking care

00:30:54.060 --> 00:30:59.910 align:middle line:84%
of, but you had no idea this
would be such a dream, fully

00:30:59.910 --> 00:31:02.160 align:middle line:84%
stepping in the
dream, fully stepping

00:31:02.160 --> 00:31:04.630 align:middle line:90%
on the heaven on earth, huh?

00:31:04.630 --> 00:31:05.530 align:middle line:90%
Gosh, no.

00:31:05.530 --> 00:31:10.410 align:middle line:84%
In fact, this has
become-- I could not have

00:31:10.410 --> 00:31:12.350 align:middle line:90%
scripted something like this.

00:31:12.350 --> 00:31:16.400 align:middle line:84%
This has just become so
much bigger than anything

00:31:16.400 --> 00:31:19.430 align:middle line:84%
I could ever have imagined
or dreamed of, ever.

00:31:19.430 --> 00:31:22.035 align:middle line:90%


00:31:22.035 --> 00:31:25.260 align:middle line:84%
I know you're sharing the
stage here with Wayne Dyer.

00:31:25.260 --> 00:31:30.920 align:middle line:84%
But your book is selling
like little pancakes.

00:31:30.920 --> 00:31:34.330 align:middle line:84%
And this is just for you,
but for you the main thing

00:31:34.330 --> 00:31:38.540 align:middle line:84%
is just being yourself,
sharing wherever it goes, even

00:31:38.540 --> 00:31:40.710 align:middle line:84%
if-- I'm sure we'll
see you very soon

00:31:40.710 --> 00:31:43.170 align:middle line:90%
on the "Oprah Winfrey Show."

00:31:43.170 --> 00:31:46.850 align:middle line:84%
There's so many different
things that when the ego is not

00:31:46.850 --> 00:31:51.020 align:middle line:90%
attached can unfold naturally.

00:31:51.020 --> 00:31:56.460 align:middle line:84%
And the thing is, I think
that people who identify too

00:31:56.460 --> 00:32:01.350 align:middle line:84%
strongly with the ego, I think
that it just comes from a place

00:32:01.350 --> 00:32:02.900 align:middle line:90%
of fear, and that's all.

00:32:02.900 --> 00:32:06.820 align:middle line:84%
And once we help people release
their fear, it's totally fine.

00:32:06.820 --> 00:32:10.630 align:middle line:84%
Because once you trust, then you
don't have to chase anything.

00:32:10.630 --> 00:32:13.400 align:middle line:84%
And right now--
and life is so much

00:32:13.400 --> 00:32:15.340 align:middle line:90%
more fun when you just allow.

00:32:15.340 --> 00:32:17.750 align:middle line:84%
Because it's really
just allowing.

00:32:17.750 --> 00:32:19.510 align:middle line:90%
It's much more relaxing.

00:32:19.510 --> 00:32:21.860 align:middle line:84%
You don't feel as
tired or as drained

00:32:21.860 --> 00:32:24.470 align:middle line:84%
because you just have
to show up and just

00:32:24.470 --> 00:32:26.770 align:middle line:90%
be yourself, be authentic.

00:32:26.770 --> 00:32:29.630 align:middle line:84%
And when you are
authentic, you will always

00:32:29.630 --> 00:32:31.640 align:middle line:90%
attract whatever's truly yours.

00:32:31.640 --> 00:32:35.430 align:middle line:84%
The real gifts will come to
you when you allow yourself

00:32:35.430 --> 00:32:37.490 align:middle line:84%
and when you dare
to be authentic.

00:32:37.490 --> 00:32:39.820 align:middle line:90%
Most of us think out of fear.

00:32:39.820 --> 00:32:43.070 align:middle line:84%
We think we have to cover
up who we are and try

00:32:43.070 --> 00:32:45.630 align:middle line:84%
and be someone else and
try and be better or try

00:32:45.630 --> 00:32:47.400 align:middle line:90%
and be like somebody else.

00:32:47.400 --> 00:32:51.230 align:middle line:84%
But that just means,
again, that we're

00:32:51.230 --> 00:32:52.820 align:middle line:84%
sending ourselves the
message that we're

00:32:52.820 --> 00:32:54.950 align:middle line:90%
not good enough as we are.

00:32:54.950 --> 00:32:57.830 align:middle line:84%
But once you are
authentic and yourself,

00:32:57.830 --> 00:33:00.800 align:middle line:84%
life actually
becomes much easier.

00:33:00.800 --> 00:33:06.380 align:middle line:84%
And as you say, for me,
it's so not about selling

00:33:06.380 --> 00:33:07.090 align:middle line:90%
books or anything.

00:33:07.090 --> 00:33:10.420 align:middle line:84%
I wouldn't care if nobody
bought a single book,

00:33:10.420 --> 00:33:13.040 align:middle line:84%
because I was sharing my
message on the internet

00:33:13.040 --> 00:33:14.470 align:middle line:90%
even before that.

00:33:14.470 --> 00:33:16.690 align:middle line:84%
And I'm just going
with the flow,

00:33:16.690 --> 00:33:18.640 align:middle line:90%
just seeing where it takes me.

00:33:18.640 --> 00:33:21.130 align:middle line:84%
Is there even--
because a lot of people

00:33:21.130 --> 00:33:22.590 align:middle line:90%
spoke of different practices.

00:33:22.590 --> 00:33:24.760 align:middle line:84%
Of course, lot of us
seen the secret at

00:33:24.760 --> 00:33:26.660 align:middle line:90%
with the law of attraction.

00:33:26.660 --> 00:33:29.010 align:middle line:84%
And this has evolved
since the secret.

00:33:29.010 --> 00:33:31.310 align:middle line:84%
I think we have brought
different pieces

00:33:31.310 --> 00:33:33.450 align:middle line:84%
about the feeling
and the allowing.

00:33:33.450 --> 00:33:36.510 align:middle line:84%
But from what I'm hearing, it's
not anymore about the vision

00:33:36.510 --> 00:33:38.310 align:middle line:90%
board or dreaming big.

00:33:38.310 --> 00:33:43.070 align:middle line:84%
Or do you actually
pray or declare or see

00:33:43.070 --> 00:33:47.560 align:middle line:84%
things or have images, or you're
just really in the allowing?

00:33:47.560 --> 00:33:48.800 align:middle line:90%
You know, it's interesting.

00:33:48.800 --> 00:33:52.100 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes I hate to
admit it, but I'm not

00:33:52.100 --> 00:33:59.040 align:middle line:84%
big into visioning or
goal setting or creating

00:33:59.040 --> 00:34:01.360 align:middle line:90%
or into prayer or intent.

00:34:01.360 --> 00:34:03.040 align:middle line:90%
I don't set my intentions.

00:34:03.040 --> 00:34:04.900 align:middle line:90%
I actually don't do any of that.

00:34:04.900 --> 00:34:08.360 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes I'm
afraid to admit that,

00:34:08.360 --> 00:34:10.469 align:middle line:84%
but I actually
don't do any of it.

00:34:10.469 --> 00:34:12.010 align:middle line:90%
I just live in the moment.

00:34:12.010 --> 00:34:15.480 align:middle line:84%
I have dreams, but
to me dreams are

00:34:15.480 --> 00:34:19.159 align:middle line:84%
different from what we call
goal setting or intention

00:34:19.159 --> 00:34:20.380 align:middle line:90%
setting or anything.

00:34:20.380 --> 00:34:22.340 align:middle line:84%
Because dreams come
from the heart.

00:34:22.340 --> 00:34:25.060 align:middle line:84%
And dreams are something--
they just come.

00:34:25.060 --> 00:34:27.969 align:middle line:84%
And it's like you
can be daydreaming.

00:34:27.969 --> 00:34:29.429 align:middle line:90%
You can be still in your mind.

00:34:29.429 --> 00:34:31.989 align:middle line:84%
And then you will feel
these amazing dreams

00:34:31.989 --> 00:34:34.120 align:middle line:84%
just coming that just
pull at the heart strings.

00:34:34.120 --> 00:34:35.420 align:middle line:90%
And it's like, oh my God.

00:34:35.420 --> 00:34:37.409 align:middle line:84%
Wouldn't it be amazing
to be like that?

00:34:37.409 --> 00:34:42.409 align:middle line:84%
But I don't set any kind of
timeline or goal or anything.

00:34:42.409 --> 00:34:46.940 align:middle line:84%
Because I believe
that the past--

00:34:46.940 --> 00:34:49.989 align:middle line:84%
there's no such thing as
the past because it's gone.

00:34:49.989 --> 00:34:51.750 align:middle line:90%
The future hasn't come yet.

00:34:51.750 --> 00:34:57.610 align:middle line:84%
My only obligation is to make
the best of the present moment.

00:34:57.610 --> 00:35:02.210 align:middle line:84%
If I can find joy-- my only
obligation really is to find

00:35:02.210 --> 00:35:04.310 align:middle line:90%
joy in the present moment.

00:35:04.310 --> 00:35:08.040 align:middle line:84%
I don't have to worry about the
vision coming true or the goal.

00:35:08.040 --> 00:35:10.050 align:middle line:84%
I don't have to
worry about a thing.

00:35:10.050 --> 00:35:13.080 align:middle line:84%
Because if I can be
happy in this moment

00:35:13.080 --> 00:35:16.050 align:middle line:84%
and just find something
to be really happy about

00:35:16.050 --> 00:35:19.450 align:middle line:84%
and laugh and have
joy in this moment,

00:35:19.450 --> 00:35:23.840 align:middle line:84%
if my only focus is this
moment, then my future

00:35:23.840 --> 00:35:25.710 align:middle line:90%
is automatically taken care of.

00:35:25.710 --> 00:35:30.600 align:middle line:84%
Because what is your future but
a collection of present moments

00:35:30.600 --> 00:35:31.910 align:middle line:90%
going forward?

00:35:31.910 --> 00:35:34.460 align:middle line:84%
So our only
obligation is to find

00:35:34.460 --> 00:35:37.940 align:middle line:84%
joy in this present
moment, and nothing more.

00:35:37.940 --> 00:35:40.290 align:middle line:84%
And your future
is taken care of.

00:35:40.290 --> 00:35:42.510 align:middle line:84%
There is a bad news,
a challenging news,

00:35:42.510 --> 00:35:45.950 align:middle line:84%
how do you react now or how
would you like to react?

00:35:45.950 --> 00:35:47.580 align:middle line:90%
I would have to take it in.

00:35:47.580 --> 00:35:51.960 align:middle line:84%
And life is what it is, and
we do deal with challenges.

00:35:51.960 --> 00:35:54.910 align:middle line:84%
And I will allow
myself to feel whatever

00:35:54.910 --> 00:35:59.370 align:middle line:84%
I feel, whether it's sadness,
whether I need to grieve.

00:35:59.370 --> 00:36:01.160 align:middle line:90%
I will grieve.

00:36:01.160 --> 00:36:03.841 align:middle line:84%
I will allow myself to
feel everything and not

00:36:03.841 --> 00:36:04.540 align:middle line:90%
judge myself.

00:36:04.540 --> 00:36:07.600 align:middle line:90%


00:36:07.600 --> 00:36:10.360 align:middle line:84%
Holding back from
whatever emotion is there.

00:36:10.360 --> 00:36:11.130 align:middle line:90%
Exactly.

00:36:11.130 --> 00:36:14.190 align:middle line:84%
I don't hold back
from many emotion.

00:36:14.190 --> 00:36:18.240 align:middle line:84%
I tend not to feel things
like guilt and regret.

00:36:18.240 --> 00:36:21.880 align:middle line:84%
Because if we live life to
the fullest in every moment,

00:36:21.880 --> 00:36:24.190 align:middle line:90%
we have nothing to regret.

00:36:24.190 --> 00:36:27.640 align:middle line:84%
But if I'm feeling sad,
I allow it to pass.

00:36:27.640 --> 00:36:33.220 align:middle line:84%
Many people feel that when
we feel that our thoughts

00:36:33.220 --> 00:36:35.840 align:middle line:84%
create our reality,
we tend to suppress

00:36:35.840 --> 00:36:37.350 align:middle line:90%
the thoughts we don't like.

00:36:37.350 --> 00:36:38.850 align:middle line:90%
I don't suppress anything.

00:36:38.850 --> 00:36:41.160 align:middle line:90%
If I feel sad, I will feel sad.

00:36:41.160 --> 00:36:43.610 align:middle line:84%
I may not go out and
meet people and show

00:36:43.610 --> 00:36:47.190 align:middle line:84%
them I'm feeling lousy, but I
will allow myself to feel it.

00:36:47.190 --> 00:36:50.611 align:middle line:84%
And when you allow your
feelings, they pass.

00:36:50.611 --> 00:36:52.170 align:middle line:84%
-Really fast.
-Yeah, they do.

00:36:52.170 --> 00:36:53.920 align:middle line:90%
And the sun comes out again.

00:36:53.920 --> 00:36:57.800 align:middle line:84%
But when you suppress them and
you try and convince yourself

00:36:57.800 --> 00:36:59.680 align:middle line:84%
you're not having
those feelings,

00:36:59.680 --> 00:37:02.140 align:middle line:84%
they linger for a long time,
because they're pushing back.

00:37:02.140 --> 00:37:04.240 align:middle line:84%
And you're pushing them down
and they're pushing back.

00:37:04.240 --> 00:37:07.200 align:middle line:84%
So you get into this
kind of entanglement,

00:37:07.200 --> 00:37:09.030 align:middle line:90%
this battle with your feelings.

00:37:09.030 --> 00:37:10.020 align:middle line:90%
I don't battle them.

00:37:10.020 --> 00:37:11.450 align:middle line:90%
I don't judge them.

00:37:11.450 --> 00:37:12.470 align:middle line:90%
I just allow them.

00:37:12.470 --> 00:37:13.700 align:middle line:90%
It's just a part of life.

00:37:13.700 --> 00:37:17.060 align:middle line:84%
It's a facet of who I
am, and it will pass.

00:37:17.060 --> 00:37:21.410 align:middle line:84%
Those are great, great lessons
there that you're giving us.

00:37:21.410 --> 00:37:22.280 align:middle line:90%
And it feels right.

00:37:22.280 --> 00:37:26.760 align:middle line:84%
It feels so right to say that,
even regarding the practices.

00:37:26.760 --> 00:37:28.620 align:middle line:84%
I'm not just saying
it to myself.

00:37:28.620 --> 00:37:31.610 align:middle line:84%
The more throughout my journey
as I started opening my heart

00:37:31.610 --> 00:37:35.350 align:middle line:84%
and feeling the love, this
is what's the most important

00:37:35.350 --> 00:37:36.070 align:middle line:90%
in the end.

00:37:36.070 --> 00:37:38.610 align:middle line:84%
The meditation, all of
that-- we do that when we're

00:37:38.610 --> 00:37:39.920 align:middle line:90%
in the present moment anyway.

00:37:39.920 --> 00:37:43.100 align:middle line:84%
And we enjoy what we do.
-Yes.

00:37:43.100 --> 00:37:46.920 align:middle line:84%
Every time when you're actually
feeling joyful, when you're

00:37:46.920 --> 00:37:49.490 align:middle line:84%
in that feeling,
that feeling place,

00:37:49.490 --> 00:37:52.470 align:middle line:84%
you're actually creating
the future already.

00:37:52.470 --> 00:37:56.840 align:middle line:84%
That is the feeling
that keeps you-- that

00:37:56.840 --> 00:38:00.460 align:middle line:84%
is your only obligation is
to find that feeling that

00:38:00.460 --> 00:38:01.940 align:middle line:90%
brings you joy.

00:38:01.940 --> 00:38:05.880 align:middle line:84%
And if you just do that, just
make the best of every moment.

00:38:05.880 --> 00:38:09.710 align:middle line:84%
Live your life to the fullest,
even if it means drinking

00:38:09.710 --> 00:38:11.200 align:middle line:90%
champagne and eating chocolate.

00:38:11.200 --> 00:38:14.490 align:middle line:84%
Because one thing I want people
to know is that a lot of people

00:38:14.490 --> 00:38:18.290 align:middle line:84%
think that certain things
more spiritual than others.

00:38:18.290 --> 00:38:20.270 align:middle line:90%
You are a spiritual being.

00:38:20.270 --> 00:38:22.020 align:middle line:90%
You cannot not be.

00:38:22.020 --> 00:38:22.990 align:middle line:90%
We just are we.

00:38:22.990 --> 00:38:25.470 align:middle line:84%
We don't have to work
hard at being spiritual.

00:38:25.470 --> 00:38:27.190 align:middle line:84%
That's another thing
I used to fear.

00:38:27.190 --> 00:38:30.150 align:middle line:84%
I used to think I had to
work hard at being spiritual.

00:38:30.150 --> 00:38:32.050 align:middle line:90%
I now realize I don't.

00:38:32.050 --> 00:38:33.680 align:middle line:90%
We are spiritual beings.

00:38:33.680 --> 00:38:35.790 align:middle line:84%
Being yourself and
being spiritual

00:38:35.790 --> 00:38:37.510 align:middle line:90%
is one and the same thing.

00:38:37.510 --> 00:38:41.000 align:middle line:84%
Lilou, who travels around the
world interviewing people,

00:38:41.000 --> 00:38:43.500 align:middle line:84%
you are a beautiful, spiritual
being for doing that.

00:38:43.500 --> 00:38:44.990 align:middle line:90%
And that's who you are.

00:38:44.990 --> 00:38:46.560 align:middle line:90%
So enjoy it.

00:38:46.560 --> 00:38:48.290 align:middle line:90%
Enjoy being who you are.

00:38:48.290 --> 00:38:52.980 align:middle line:84%
And whether you are a
scientist or a Mother Teresa

00:38:52.980 --> 00:38:56.700 align:middle line:84%
or a monk on a mountaintop,
we're all spiritual.

00:38:56.700 --> 00:38:58.170 align:middle line:90%
We're all equal.

00:38:58.170 --> 00:39:00.070 align:middle line:84%
And it's less about
the rituals rules

00:39:00.070 --> 00:39:04.170 align:middle line:84%
or even-- where you
religious in the past?

00:39:04.170 --> 00:39:07.140 align:middle line:84%
I grew up with
parents who taught me

00:39:07.140 --> 00:39:09.030 align:middle line:90%
many Hindu rituals and things.

00:39:09.030 --> 00:39:10.740 align:middle line:90%
There's a lot of rituals.

00:39:10.740 --> 00:39:13.020 align:middle line:84%
Yes, there are
a lot of rituals.

00:39:13.020 --> 00:39:17.330 align:middle line:84%
But again, because I had such
a mixed cultural upbringing,

00:39:17.330 --> 00:39:19.200 align:middle line:84%
a lot of things brought
me a lot of fear,

00:39:19.200 --> 00:39:21.620 align:middle line:84%
because I learned
many Chinese things.

00:39:21.620 --> 00:39:25.380 align:middle line:84%
I learned many Western things,
like Western religious things.

00:39:25.380 --> 00:39:27.960 align:middle line:84%
I was in a Catholic school
for a very short time.

00:39:27.960 --> 00:39:32.510 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of things
contradict each other.

00:39:32.510 --> 00:39:36.330 align:middle line:84%
And that's what caused
a lot of fear in me,

00:39:36.330 --> 00:39:38.440 align:middle line:84%
is that you cannot
spend your whole

00:39:38.440 --> 00:39:43.290 align:middle line:84%
life just doing rituals of every
possible religion and culture.

00:39:43.290 --> 00:39:46.340 align:middle line:84%
And when you're exposed to
so many, what do you do?

00:39:46.340 --> 00:39:47.700 align:middle line:90%
What do you follow?

00:39:47.700 --> 00:39:54.460 align:middle line:84%
And it was in that pure state
that I was in that I realized

00:39:54.460 --> 00:39:57.280 align:middle line:84%
no matter what, even
if I don't follow

00:39:57.280 --> 00:40:00.070 align:middle line:84%
a single ritual for
the rest of my life,

00:40:00.070 --> 00:40:02.200 align:middle line:90%
I am still a spiritual being.

00:40:02.200 --> 00:40:07.390 align:middle line:84%
I'm still a divine,
magnificent spiritual being who

00:40:07.390 --> 00:40:10.740 align:middle line:90%
deserves to live a joyful life.

00:40:10.740 --> 00:40:13.030 align:middle line:90%
And that was the discovery.

00:40:13.030 --> 00:40:15.860 align:middle line:84%
In Hindu traditions,
there's a lot of the karma.

00:40:15.860 --> 00:40:16.840 align:middle line:90%
You speak a lot of the karma.

00:40:16.840 --> 00:40:20.220 align:middle line:84%
Did you think at some point
that you had this because

00:40:20.220 --> 00:40:22.540 align:middle line:84%
of your karma, because
you had been a bad girl

00:40:22.540 --> 00:40:25.140 align:middle line:84%
in this life and past lives?
-Yeah.

00:40:25.140 --> 00:40:27.230 align:middle line:90%
I had thought many things.

00:40:27.230 --> 00:40:29.620 align:middle line:84%
I partly believed it
was because of my karma.

00:40:29.620 --> 00:40:31.700 align:middle line:84%
And I hated that
feeling, because when

00:40:31.700 --> 00:40:33.240 align:middle line:84%
you feel it's your
karma, you feel there's

00:40:33.240 --> 00:40:35.650 align:middle line:90%
nothing you can do about it.

00:40:35.650 --> 00:40:38.280 align:middle line:84%
I deserve it because
of something I

00:40:38.280 --> 00:40:41.320 align:middle line:84%
did in a past life, which
I don't even remember,

00:40:41.320 --> 00:40:42.760 align:middle line:90%
but I deserve it.

00:40:42.760 --> 00:40:47.750 align:middle line:84%
And so I had different people
tell me different things.

00:40:47.750 --> 00:40:50.080 align:middle line:84%
There were people that
said, oh, you created it.

00:40:50.080 --> 00:40:51.810 align:middle line:90%
Your thoughts created it.

00:40:51.810 --> 00:40:54.250 align:middle line:84%
And that made me really
scared of my thoughts.

00:40:54.250 --> 00:40:55.250 align:middle line:90%
I thought, oh, my God.

00:40:55.250 --> 00:40:56.610 align:middle line:90%
My thoughts created this?

00:40:56.610 --> 00:41:00.170 align:middle line:84%
So I started to get really
scared of my thoughts.

00:41:00.170 --> 00:41:04.820 align:middle line:84%
And so there were all these
things that really scared me.

00:41:04.820 --> 00:41:10.060 align:middle line:84%
And in that awake state was
when I realized that all

00:41:10.060 --> 00:41:13.090 align:middle line:90%
I have to do is love myself.

00:41:13.090 --> 00:41:16.890 align:middle line:84%
It's not my thoughts
about cancer and so on.

00:41:16.890 --> 00:41:20.496 align:middle line:84%
But it starts from first,
how do I feel about myself?

00:41:20.496 --> 00:41:23.840 align:middle line:90%


00:41:23.840 --> 00:41:27.700 align:middle line:84%
Do I love and respect myself
that I don't allow other people

00:41:27.700 --> 00:41:31.370 align:middle line:84%
to abuse me, or do I
forsake myself or do

00:41:31.370 --> 00:41:33.560 align:middle line:90%
I treat myself like a doormat?

00:41:33.560 --> 00:41:34.380 align:middle line:90%
It's that.

00:41:34.380 --> 00:41:38.780 align:middle line:84%
It's allowing yourself to be
the magnificence that you are.

00:41:38.780 --> 00:41:41.620 align:middle line:84%
What I find amazing and
I've witnessed quite often

00:41:41.620 --> 00:41:45.240 align:middle line:84%
in what I do is that when we
give ourselves the permission

00:41:45.240 --> 00:41:48.080 align:middle line:84%
to do something, or, oh,
today I deserve a massage,

00:41:48.080 --> 00:41:51.280 align:middle line:84%
or today I deserve this, and
you really treat yourself

00:41:51.280 --> 00:41:57.030 align:middle line:84%
with love, then there
is this instantaneous--

00:41:57.030 --> 00:42:00.440 align:middle line:84%
I would receive a check or
something to compensate that,

00:42:00.440 --> 00:42:02.380 align:middle line:84%
like immediately the
universe saying, yeah.

00:42:02.380 --> 00:42:03.910 align:middle line:90%
But you did the first step.

00:42:03.910 --> 00:42:06.270 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, exactly.
Exactly.

00:42:06.270 --> 00:42:09.131 align:middle line:84%
The universe confirms
to you that you--

00:42:09.131 --> 00:42:10.570 align:middle line:84%
-Once you do it.
-Yeah.

00:42:10.570 --> 00:42:11.269 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:42:11.269 --> 00:42:14.840 align:middle line:84%
Because first you have to kind
of say, I'm worthy of this.

00:42:14.840 --> 00:42:16.540 align:middle line:84%
And then the
universe will confirm

00:42:16.540 --> 00:42:17.740 align:middle line:90%
that to you, that you are.

00:42:17.740 --> 00:42:20.590 align:middle line:84%
But if you say, oh,
I'm not worthy of it--

00:42:20.590 --> 00:42:21.900 align:middle line:90%
I'm waiting for a sign.

00:42:21.900 --> 00:42:24.010 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, I'm waiting for a sign.

00:42:24.010 --> 00:42:26.130 align:middle line:84%
It's not going to come,
because if you're waiting

00:42:26.130 --> 00:42:27.710 align:middle line:84%
it means you don't
feel you're worthy.

00:42:27.710 --> 00:42:30.460 align:middle line:84%
You want something from
the outside to show you

00:42:30.460 --> 00:42:31.660 align:middle line:90%
you're worthy.

00:42:31.660 --> 00:42:35.061 align:middle line:84%
You have to feel it and know
it and know it from in here.

00:42:35.061 --> 00:42:35.760 align:middle line:90%
You're worthy.

00:42:35.760 --> 00:42:38.620 align:middle line:84%
The fact that you
exist-- life is a gift.

00:42:38.620 --> 00:42:40.220 align:middle line:90%
It's an absolute gift.

00:42:40.220 --> 00:42:42.180 align:middle line:84%
And the fact that
you have this gift,

00:42:42.180 --> 00:42:46.305 align:middle line:84%
you are one lucky,
magnificent human being.

00:42:46.305 --> 00:42:47.780 align:middle line:90%
You really are.

00:42:47.780 --> 00:42:49.390 align:middle line:84%
And you have to
treat it that way.

00:42:49.390 --> 00:42:52.090 align:middle line:84%
And so just live
life to the fullest.

00:42:52.090 --> 00:42:55.950 align:middle line:84%
And when you can do that
and find that place of joy,

00:42:55.950 --> 00:42:58.250 align:middle line:84%
the universe will
actually match it.

00:42:58.250 --> 00:43:00.630 align:middle line:90%
It'll confirm it to you.

00:43:00.630 --> 00:43:03.210 align:middle line:84%
And we've been living
the other way around.

00:43:03.210 --> 00:43:06.660 align:middle line:84%
We've been doing, doing,
doing, in order to have

00:43:06.660 --> 00:43:09.230 align:middle line:84%
and then be one day happy.
-Yes.

00:43:09.230 --> 00:43:10.440 align:middle line:90%
And this is the problem.

00:43:10.440 --> 00:43:13.680 align:middle line:84%
